    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A casting technique in which metal is poured into a piece moldmade of a specific type of sand that is bound by clay (or oil or resinin modern foundries). The piece mold is made by ramming thesand around a rigid model or chef-modèle within stacked metalframes.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
